I'm using dlscript to bind Godot with Python. However I couldn't find how to retrieve the globals constants (i.g. `KEY_ESCAPE`):

Given `GlobalConstants` class is not registered inside ClassDB, it is not possible to retrieve  `GlobalConstants.get_global_constant_*` methods with `godot_method_bind_get_method`.

On top of that, dlscript doesn't provide custom functions to access  `GlobalConstants.get_global_constant_*`.

I would feel the latter would be the simpler way to solve this, for example by adding to `dlscript/godot.cpp`:
```c
const int GDAPI godot_get_global_constant_count() {
       return GlobalConstants::get_global_constant_count();
}

const char GDAPI *godot_get_global_constant_name(int index) {
       return GlobalConstants::get_global_constant_name(index);
}

int GDAPI godot_get_global_constant_value(int index) {
       return GlobalConstants::get_global_constant_value(index);
}
```

Backport @bojidar-bg's #6292 PR which implements enums like:

```
enum MONTHS {JAN, FEB}
enum NUMBERS {NEG=-1, ZERO, ONE, TWO, FIVE=5, SIX}
enum {FIRST=1, SECOND=2, THIRD=3, FIFTH=5}
```

Small demo/test project here: [enum_test.tar.gz](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/files/903406/enum_test.tar.gz)
